title: Grateful Dead Live at Curtis Hixon Convention Hall on 1973-12-19
lineage: Dat (Sony R500) -> Sound Devices 744T -> Samplitude Professional v10.2 -> FLAC
description:
Set 1: Promised Land, Sugaree, Mexicali Blues, Sugar Shack, Dire Wolf, Black Throated Wind, Candyman, Jack Straw, Big Railroad Blues, Big River, Here Comes Sunshine, El Paso, Ramble On Rose, Playing In The Band

Set 2: Mississippi Half-Step Uptown Toodeloo, Me And Bobby McGee, Weather Report Suite Prelude > Weather Report Suite Part 1 > Let It Grow, He's Gone > Truckin' > Nobody's Fault But Mine > Truckin' > Stella Blue > Around and Around, Casey Jones

From Wikipedia
Curtis Hixon Hall was Tampa's primary concert venue from the mid-1960s until the early 1980s, 
Notable shows included:
Jimi Hendrix played Curtis Hixon Hall twice in 1968, on August 16 and November 23.
In between those dates, The Jimi Hendrix Experience released their #1 charting album Electric Ladyland.
Janis Joplin was arrested by the Tampa Police for "obscenity" while playing a show with B.B. King and others in the hall on November 16, 1969.
Duane Allman made one of only two public performances with Eric Clapton and Derek and the Dominos in the hall on December 1, 1970.
*****AND DON"T FORGET
The GRATEFUL DEAD..
December 18 &19 of 1973
Curtis Hixon Hall was demolished in 1993, and the land was converted into a public park. 
The park was redesigned and incorporated into the Tampa Riverwalk in 2010, and the facility's former footprint is now home to the Tampa Museum of Art, the Glazer Children’s Museum, and the northern portions of Curtis Hixon Waterfront Park.

Dicks Picks #1 Yeah, when Dick Latvala picked this show to start his Dicks Picks he definitely picked a good one. He could have done just as well by picking the previous night in my personal opinion. This night & 12-18-73 are actually bookmarked on my phone and I listen to one of them at the very least once a week. That is, in between hearing stuff that "Wall of Sound" & "okiedeadhead" have put out on YouTube. The best track on here is Here Comes Sunshine. As someone else put it in a different review, the Here Comes Sunshine was well worth the price of admission alone. And o  12-18 Greatest Story Ever Told is one of my favorite tracks. I listen to it quite a lot.
12 20 2023 playing thru Fender Red Knob, what a box of chocolate to open. Ear Candy
